name: KING GIZZARD One-Off Acoustic Weird-Stuff Night
description:
Brazilian Pop/Rock scene from the 80’s, 90’s and 00’s

Formed in Sydney in 2019, Innoqua Brazilis recollects the best of Brazilian Pop/Rock scene from the 80’s, 90’s and 00’s. Join us to celebrate the end of 2021 and sing along to classics from Legião Urbana, Paralamas do Sucesso, Charlie Brown Jr, Skank, Titãs, Jota Quest, Mamonas and more.


Leandro Magalhães - Drums & Backing Vocals,  Carlos Barboza - Guitar,  Zé Andrade - Vocals,  Paul Golobocov - Bass Guitar & Backing Vocals & Flávio Oliveira - Lead Guitar

Level 1 is the intimate room

$25 entry includes band and a meal  of your choice

7pm doors
8.30pm band

Lazybones Lounge Restaurant & Bar is a  COVID Safe ✅. You must follow the conditions of entry

name: SIR ARCHER W/GUESTS HONEY NOTHINGS + KEENS MUSTARD (SELLING FAST)
description:
Fresher than the Colonel’s chicken. Hotter than a seatbelt in summer. Tastier than sticky date pudding and ice-cream. OK, not quite! 

With the July release of their four-track EP, The Feast, comes a deeper look into what makes Sir Archer, well... Sir Archer. 

A group that plays with the perfect balance and maturity to achieve a fresh sound smothered in vintage tones. Their ability to harness the playing power of seven musicians into well-crafted songs and create a show full of energy is a Sir Archer signature.

Supported by two of Sydney's finest, Honey Nothings and Keen's Mustard

name: SHRUB COMEDY II
description:
Shrub Comedy is back!

Melbourne's finest night of alternative comedy is back!

Sketch, Stand-up, Drag, Circus, Absurdity, characters & free pizza. We know you're not ready, but it's here. Congratulations. Don't shrub the small stuff.  

Featuring: Annie and Lena Aurelia St Clair Burton Brothers Jude Perl Oliver Coleman Tina Del Twist MC: Patrick Collins 

Doors at 7pm, $15 tickets, free pizza.  

Kepler's Yard, 24 Moons, Northcote.  

Shrub Comedy takes place on unceded Wurundjeri/Kulin land.
